===Etymology===
From Early Modern English {{term|familie|lang=en}} (not in Middle English), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|familia||the servants in a household, domestics collectively|lang=la}}, from {{term|famulus||servant|lang=la}}/{{term|famula||female servant|lang=la}}, from Old Latin {{term|famul|lang=la}}, of obscure origin. Perhaps derived from or cognate to {{etyl|osc|en}} {{term|famel||servant|lang=osc}}.

